-- Saudi Water Executive to Head International Desalination Group
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-10-21T12:22:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-21/saudi-water-executive-to-head-international-desalination-group.html
A Saudi water executive, Abdullah
al-Alshaikh, deputy governor for planning of the kingdom’s
biggest desalinator, has been named president of the
International Desalination Association.  The announcement of the appointment of the state-owned
Saline Water Conversion Corp. official by the IDA group that’s
associated with the  United Nations  took place as the 2013 IDA
World Congress is meeting Oct. 20-Oct. 25 in Tianjin, China.  Saudi Arabia  is the largest seawater desalination country
by commissioned capacity, mostly for energy industry needs and a
growing population, ahead of the United Arab Emirates, according
to IDA data published this month. Spain is third.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
